place_description: Locally owned café and coffee bar offering breakfast, lunch and custom crafted coffees in our relaxing dine-in space and outside patios. Our menu features made to order omelets, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, grain bowls, empanadas, burgers, wraps, and salads as well as vegetarian options and many café classics. Our espresso bar uses locally roasted, sustainably sourced beans from Magnolia Coffee in our Nitro, cold brew, specialty coffee drinks and retail whole bean coffees. We also serve protein shakes, frappes, smoothies, and fitness drinks. Are you looking to host an event or party? Come check out our venue spaces inside our café and neighboring co-work. We also offer full-service catering through our sister company TreeTop Catering.

reviews_data.review_text: My boyfriend and I stopped by today for a quick snack before heading out. The manager was at the register and was incredibly friendly. He recommended the empanadas, mentioning they're a top seller, so we decided to try them. We got the chicken, guava and cheese, and beef empanadas, which came with a cilantro dip. They were delicious--some of the best empanadas I've ever had and not a bad price either! Definitely coming back again!
This place was a really nice find. Perfect to catch up with a friend. Good foods and lots of sweet coffee options.

Wish we lived closer to this place so we could come more often! The breakfast wrap is outstanding, the baked goods are lovely, and the drinks are great too. Everything always comes out perfectly and the staff is excellent.
Love this place! Great atmosphere, coffee is delicious, and portions are huge. Employees are super nice too!

As I waited at Jiffy Lube in Matthews, NC, I stumbled upon a hidden gem right around the corner--an exquisite coffee shop and restaurant that turned out to be a delightful surprise. From the moment I stepped inside The Collective Cafe, I knew I was in for a culinary treat.

The ambiance of the place was warm and inviting, with its cozy decor and comfortable seating. The aroma of freshly brewed coffee filled the air, instantly tantalizing my senses. The friendly and attentive staff greeted me with genuine smiles, making me feel right at home.

Being a coffee lover, I couldn't resist trying their specialty brews. The barista expertly prepared my cappuccino, and with the first sip, I was transported to coffee heaven. The smooth, rich flavors and perfect balance of the espresso and velvety foam were simply divine. It was evident that they took great pride in their coffee craftsmanship.

As I perused the menu, I discovered a wide array of delectable dishes to choose from. The menu showcased a fusion of international flavors, promising a culinary adventure. The presentation was impeccable, and with every bite, I savored the explosion of tastes and textures. It was evident that the chef had a passion for creating culinary masterpieces.

What truly impressed me was their commitment to sourcing local and organic ingredients. They emphasized sustainability and showcased seasonal produce, which added an extra layer of freshness and vibrancy to each dish. The attention to detail was evident not only in the taste but also in the visual appeal of the food.

The service was exceptional throughout my visit. The staff members were knowledgeable about the menu, and they were more than willing to provide recommendations based on personal preferences. The wait time for my food was minimal, and my server ensured that I had everything I needed to make my dining experience memorable.

Overall, my unplanned visit turned out to be a culinary adventure that surpassed my expectations. The combination of exceptional coffee, tantalizing flavors, and attentive service made it a standout dining experience in Matthews, NC. Whether you're seeking a cozy coffee spot or a place to indulge in extraordinary cuisine, I highly recommend visiting this place. It's a true gem that deserves recognition for its outstanding culinary offerings and warm hospitality.

I used to really love this place, and I still do to some extent. I love the veggie scramble wrap. I still order it, but there's one problem. This dish is supposed to come with salsa and a fruit cup. It used to consistently always be delivered with both of those items, but in the past few months there is now only a 10% chance that, if ordered, the wrap will come with salsa and a fruit cup. More often than not, I only get the wrap. It's pretty disappointing, because the salsa essentially made that wrap so delicious. Without it, it's rather bland. I make do by adding salt or my own hot sauce, but it isn't the same. Additionally, in the past few months every single time I get this wrap, it has been increasingly greasy. When I pick it up, it literally drips grease. "No problem," I thought initially, "I'll just wipe up the excess with a napkin." Nope. It's as if the grease is coming from some source of infinite grease within the wrap. I wish they would pay more attention when making these, and when packing them up for delivery. It makes it less enjoyable when they don't. I don't know if they got a new cook/chef recently, or what, but if that is the case, I hope they get them trained up pretty soon. I miss my yummy veggie scramble wrap.

Presley makes a fabulous slushy, she's the best!!
Atmosphere was awful as was the food and the service was slow. The cook didn't wear a beard guard. Food was also ala  carte which caused our lunch for two to be $28. Would not recommend.
The service here is wonderful plus the food and coffee is superb. The whole vibe of this place is very inviting and the argentinian empanadas are my favorite!

We visited for the first time today for brunch, and it was good! The atmosphere was really nice with lots of room inside and outside. The coffee was GREAT, and the food was pretty good but nothing special. We will definitely come back!
Very good food and great service. Amazing atmosphere
Great coffee and food! Friendly and fast service and great atmosphere. Really the perfect place to work on school, art, or anything else.
Good if you like Jesus, otherwise just fine

The brightly colored menu and general hipster aesthetic kind of led me to believe that the food was going more nutrition forward.  It was basically bacon, eggs and feta cheese being promoted as health food.
Good place and woker.
Such a cute vibe, amazing food and a great idea! Staff was phenomenal!
Very unique concept to meeting people and have meeting or simply workspace for a few hours
Delicious, great service, comfortable atmosphere...

Super chill spot! Great local coffee and tasty brunch. Lots of room and options for tables, comfy chairs, and bartops. Won't be able to get here too often except on Saturdays due to their current hours, but ill definitely be frequenting it when i can.

The staff are very friendly and patient. We spoke with, I believe, the owner or maybe main manager? Very informative and hungry for feedback. These are good things!!!
Superb

This is an excellent restaurant nothing but great people and the owner he is such a wonderful person checking up on his staff and loyal customers!! And the food is always on point   this is a must !!! I love their empanadas and their tenders. I have always had a great experience with the people and food  I highly recommend this restaurant.
Great food, friendly people, amazing atmosphere. You can go for breakfast, lunch, a coffee or just to hang out. Good place to work or read. Highly recommend. Oh, and I love the daily specials.

My friends and I were visiting from Florida and the atmosphere was so peaceful and calm. Great for students or business people to be productive. Most of the food is prepared in house and the coffee was delicious. Prices are reasonable for how good the food is. The employees were so sweet and always doing something like cleaning the tables. Would definitely visit this cafe if I ever return to NC!!!

This place really is a hidden gem. I found them via grubhub, and I order often. Their drinks frappes are excellent, and their 1lb chicken salad is worth every penny. I am only leaving 3 stars bc the last two times I ordered a side has been missing, and the food just hasn't seemed as fresh. Specifically the breakfast sammie on croissant which is normally my favorite. This recent time I tried the cinnamon rolls and they were very dry and didn't seem fresh. I am not going to give up on them yet, and hoping for a better experience next time.
Great food, good coffee, nice ambiance
I love this place! Friendly staff, great food (healthy) and very clean.
Great environment, friendly staff
Associates were very nice and the food was delicious! Love the strawberry smoothie.
Had lunch and I am thinking this is my new lunch place.  The atmosphere and food and associates was Awesome. So glad i had a friend to tell me about this place.

Hidden gem. Welcoming space, baristas are very accommodating and hospitable with groups. Coffee's great, but the delicious food is what sets it apart. I would definitely grab breakfast here, the 'Fill Me Up' wrap is consistently delicious. Fast internet.
Very nice, comfortable cafe to hang out. Comfortable couches and chairs, quiet atmosphere, great service. I can definitely see myself meeting a friend here or doing work on my computer.

They're a long way from where I live, but the food was excellent it was worth the drive . I ordered my food to go. They had my order right just the way l want it .The customer service was excellent. The young lady was nice and friendly and answered my questions, because this was the first time I ever been to this restaurant. I will go again when this pandemic is over so I can go inside and sit down and eat because the atmosphere seems very nice and pleasant.

This place is a hidden gem for now. I love everything about it. The vibes, coffee, food and co-working space. I'm excited to hang and work out of here more. It's a bonus that's it 3 minutes from the gym I workout at too!
Nice scene to relax, eat, and drink some good coffee. The make your own omelette was delicious. Highly recommended.
Very friendly staff. The have gluten free bread too! The food is so fresh and delish!  Be patient because they make it to order.
The service was ellecent as always. My wife enjoyed her veggie omelette. Great atmosphere always enjoy the experience.
Friendly service; entertaining decor; good food.
Very comfortable, clean atmosphere. They're also really good to their customers, and the coffee is good. I highly recommend!
Empanadas were awesome!

Very cozy and welcoming atmosphere as soon as you walk in. Staff was extremely friendly. I ordered a yogurt parfait, an iced coffee, and a sandwich which i cant remember the name of but very similar to a caprice sandwich. Everything was delicious, the yogurt parfait was creamy with plenty of fruit with some granola and a touch of what tasted like local wildflower honey, the iced coffee actually tasted of coffee instead of sugar syrup and wasnt 99% ice either, the sandwich was perfectly balanced in flavor and texture, they used fresh mozzarella that was soft and delicate but flavorful with fresh basil and very soft and ripe tomatoes. Will definitely be visiting again soon.

If you are looking for a hometown feel, great people and wonderful food, this is the place. I have never had a bad experience coming here and look forward to every time I am able to visit. A must stop.
Great place to relax, enjoy meaningful conversation, and enjoy a pastry.
The best... The food is really good... The staff is nice and polite... Love this cafe...
Great atmosphere and friendly staff. Do yourself a favor and buy some empanadas!

HOW HAVE I NOT BEEN HERE?! If you're seeking a quiet workspace space with top of the line coffee, plus with staff who actually understand the craft of coffee, and outstanding food YOU NEED TO GET HERE! I'm officially making myself a regular.

Let me also add the staff here are Chick-Fil-A level of customer service!
This is such a perfect cafe! I'm so glad to have discovered it. Highly recommend eating here and they have delicious milkshakes. I am so excited for them to open an outdoor area and a park!
The food was amazing and the staff was friendly
Great food, great atmosphere, and friendly staff and owner. I'd toy haven't tried it, you should.
The staff is so friendly! I love going here for coffee and lunch. I highly recommend getting their empanadas because they're the best I've had!! Inside the shop is adorable too :)
Great food and service
Food is great.  Fabulous staff!
This cafe is such an amazing atmosphere with FANTASTIC food!

Wow!  Made my first visit to Collective Cafe today and will be returning!  That was the best Cobb Salad I've ever eaten.  Spoke to a gentleman while waiting for my salad (forgot to ask his name) and he made me more excited to return.  Such a nice variety of healthy and not so healthy items to.choose from.
The chicken was delicious, greens super fresh, salad dressing just yummy.

Fantastic atmosphere and the coffee is great! The owner is really welcoming and passionate and the rest of the team is wonderful as well. I just came for coffee today but the food looks great. I will definitely be back for coffee and a meal!
Great for breakfast delivery.

I haven't eaten in the restaurant yet, but completely enjoyed the dinner Briley Apartments provided to the residents tonight.  food was excellent and the Ladies in the leasing office have told me how great the rest of the menu is.  I'll definitely be checking it out in person!!

I have not been to the physical restaurant, but I order their food on Door Dash often. Everything I have tried from here has been amazing! The quantity and quality of the food is well worth what you pay. They have a great selection of menu items, and for a foodie what more could you ask for!
The name of the sandwich is Generous Turkey Sandwich.  Maybe there was a turkey shortage because I got half a slice broken into pieces and spread out.  Literally called Generous Turkey.

As foodies that like something different/unique and healthy, we absolutely feel in love with this place. Not only is the food absolutely delicious and high-quality, it's the perfect quick meal choice that the entire family loves.  Also the staff is awesome!
Rico

This is my new favorite spot for breakfast or lunch! The atmosphere is quaint and welcoming, the staff is friendly, helpful and fast, and the food is AMAZING! The menu has so many options, it's hard to decide, and there are lots of healthy choices too. I'm looking forward to enjoying the outside patio once the temperatures are cooler. It's a hidden gem in Matthews!
Super friendly staff and a great atmosphere!
Fantastic place. Foos is excellent! Staff very friendly and helpful!
Awesome ambiance. Perfect for working or studying.
Great atmosphere for work and yummy food! Lots of seating and the staff is very friendly. 10/10
The staff is super friendly, clean place and the most amazing empanadas in town, cafe bom bom delicious other food looks really good, will come back to try other items from the menu.
Amazing! The food and drinks are scrumptious!!! Amazing service and very friendly staff! 100% recommend!!! Love it here!!!
Great atmosphere, the people there are fantastic, excellent food and coffee. Definitely recommend.
Really impressed with this place. The food is delicious, well made and the prices are great. Get the iced mocha!

Honestly my favorite place in all of South Charlotte! Can't express how friendly and welcoming they were. Staff is amazing, made me feel like a valued customer. I haven't even started on the coffee and the food menu ;)

HAILEY was quick to accommodate! I drink decaf after 1 cup and i had already had a regular cup today. Besides brewing a pot of decaf just for me, she also went and found a few flavored creamers for me. AWESOME experience

I've stopped by the Collective Cafe a few times since they opened for brunch, coffee, and a community yoga class. Each time, I've been very impressed with the friendliness of their staff, the delicious food, and the wonderful ambiance. I will be using their cafe for all of my upcoming coffee dates and highly recommend to my friends & family.
Really cute venue with a good ambience, delicious food, and great service. We will definitely be back.

My wife and I had lunch there yesterday. We both got their Collective burger. Very good meat and well seasoned. Great steak fries with the burger. Located behind Ridge Church. We recommend you give them a try!

This place is so cool! Great environment to study or do work and the food is on point. They even have a ping pong table and Pac-Man to decompress with. Several different rooms and even a phone booth to record podcasts in. Not to mention they are connected to a great church. Will definitely be back.

I had a last minute meeting and ran into the collective cafe to rent a work space for an hour.  The environment was incredibly inviting, the staff was very helpful and the coffee was fresh and tasty.   Thank you collective cafe team for a great experience.
